You are here:

Decision Optimization can generate optimization results in a CRM Analytics dataset. Use the dataset to explore the results and share with others.

Explore the Results Dataset

If you generate a results dataset during optimization creation, the dataset is automatically created in your “My Private App” when the optimization is saved and run successfully.

To access the results dataset:

In Analytics Studio, browse or search for the dataset.
In Model Manager, use the Optimize tab to see a list of all optimizations.
The results dataset has one row for every record included in the optimization. The Id represents the Salesforce record Id and can be used as a key.

Explore the results dataset.

The actionable variables are included, and can be dimensions or measures depending on the data type. The measure “Optimization_ [Objective Label]” is generated by the optimization and represents each record’s contribution to the goal of the optimization. If the objective label was left blank during optimization creation, it’s named “Optimization_[Objective Value]”.

The dimension Optimization_Excluded is generated by the optimization and indicates whether a record was excluded from the optimization due to missing data.

Use the Results Dataset

Use a recipe to add other data to the results dataset for analysis or to add data from the results dataset to other datasets. See https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?id=sf.bi_integrate_recipe_create.htm.

Use the Salesforce Output Connector to write data from the results dataset into a Salesforce object. See https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?id=sf.bi_integrate_connectors_output_salesforce.htm.
title: Using Salesforce Analytics for Decision Optimization
